If I may suggest, please breakdown the detail explanation into 3 separate videos. This is information overload. Very technical is OK for serious viewers. But for general public, this is what we need to know:
1. Day one -6 , PCR test shown Positive, meaning the presence of antigen at the swab location either throat or nose. If also take Rapid Test Antibody, it shows Negative first, because the body hasnt produced the antibody specific for this S-type Covid19. Cell Memory hasnt created yet for this type of covid19. 
2. Day 7 - 14 - The body showing all the signs of getting sick. Vit C, E, D3 and Zinc are needed to increase the immunity. Plus plenty of sleep, hydration, light exercises n relaxation method like meditation n music. 
3. Day 15-21 -- PCR test Neg n Rapid Test Antibodies Negative. Macrophage of our TCell won the battle against Covid19. Antibodies no longer needed, enemy got beaten. So rapid test will show NEGATIVE antibody. The patient is healthy.  
This is simplistic explanation. 

Wearing mask doesnt guarantee a person wont get exposed, but definitely will Minimize the Viral Load that each person can tolerate without getting seriously ill. Washing hands frquently. Avoiding crowd n red zoned areas. 

Socializing UNNECESSARILY is STUPID. Be smart. Be informed.
